    "description": "Wait till an object in object_list is ready. Returns the list of those objects in object_list which are ready. If timeout is a float then the call blocks for at most that many seconds. If timeout is None then it will block for an unlimited period. A negative timeout is equivalent to a zero timeout. For both POSIX and Windows, an object can appear in object_list if it is a readable Connection object; a connected and readable socket.socket object; or the sentinel attribute of a Process object. ...",
